headline: How Investors May Respond To CVS Health (CVS) Facing Tennessee Crackdown On Its Integrated Pharmacy Model
summary: In late February 2026, CVS Health warned that pending Tennessee legislation banning combined ownership of pharmacies and pharmacy benefit managers could force closure of all 134 of its state stores, MinuteClinics, and related operations, threatening thousands of jobs and patient access to care. This pushback against CVS’s vertically integrated model in Tennessee highlights growing regulatory scrutiny that could have wider implications for how large healthcare chains combine insurance, PBM,...
